The City of Joburg is intensifying its fight against drug abuse. It recently intoduced a local drug committee that would identify substance abuse hotspots.This morning we're visiting Riverlea, an area bedevilled by drug abuse. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The City of Johannesburg has appointed local drug committees to identify substance abuse hotspots. Riverlea in Johannesburg is one of the areas known for battling a substance abuse scourge. READ: EXCLUSIVE: 'Illegally' imported chloroquine probed One community leader in the area says police are complicit in the illegal drug trade. Watch the video above for more.